Common Cybersecurity Threats
Insider Threat
Description

A threat caused by employees, contractors, or trusted users who misuse their authorized access.

Possible Impact
Data theft
Financial losses
Reputation damage
Prevention
Least privilege access
Employee awareness training
Activity monitoring
Malware
Description

Malware is malicious software designed to damage, steal, or disrupt computer systems.

Possible Impact
File corruption
System downtime
Loss of sensitive information
Prevention
Install antivirus software
Keep systems updated
Avoid downloading unknown files
Phishing
Description

Phishing is a cyberattack that tricks users into revealing confidential information through fake emails or websites.

Possible Impact
Credential theft
Financial fraud
Account compromise
Prevention
Verify email authenticity
Avoid clicking suspicious links
Conduct phishing awareness training
Weak Passwords
Description

Using simple or repeated passwords makes accounts easier for attackers to compromise.

Possible Impact
Unauthorized access
Data exposure
Prevention
Use complex passwords
Enable Multi-Factor Authentication
Change passwords regularly
Unpatched Systems
Description

Software that has not been updated may contain known vulnerabilities that attackers can exploit.

Possible Impact
Malware infections
Unauthorized access
System compromise
Prevention
Regular patch management
Automatic updates
Vulnerability scanning